âœ… 1. Extended Email Notification Plugin (EXTENDED EMAIL)

The Extended E-mail Plugin (Email-ext plugin) allows Jenkins to send customized email notifications after a build completes.

ğŸ”¥ Why it is needed

The default Jenkins email is basic.
Extended Email lets you:

Send emails for SUCCESS, FAILURE, UNSTABLE, or every stage

Customize subject line, body, HTML format

Attach build logs, reports, artifacts

Apply conditions (e.g., email only on failure)

ğŸ“Œ Typical Use Case

You want developers to get notified ONLY if a build fails, with logs attached.

ğŸ“Œ Example configuration (Freestyle Job)

Post-build Actions â†’ Editable Email Notification

Recipients: team@example.com

Subject: â€œBuild ${BUILD_STATUS} for job ${JOB_NAME}â€

Content: Custom message body

Triggers: Failure â€” checked

ğŸ“Œ Pipeline example
post {
    failure {
        emailext(
            to: "team@example.com",
            subject: "Build Failed: ${env.JOB_NAME}",
            body: "Check console output: ${env.BUILD_URL}"
        )
    }
}

âœ… 2. Copy Artifact Plugin (COPY ARTIFACT)

This plugin allows one Jenkins job to copy files/artifacts from another Jenkins job.

ğŸ”¥ Why it is needed

Used in multi-stage pipelines:

BUILD â†’ TEST â†’ DEPLOY


The test job needs the artifacts created by the build job.
The deploy job needs the WAR created by the test job.

ğŸ“Œ Where used in your assignment

MavenJava_Test copies artifacts from MavenJava_Build

MavenWeb_Deploy copies artifacts from MavenWeb_Test

ğŸ“Œ Example configuration

In job â†’ Build Step â†’ Copy artifacts from another project

Project name: MavenWeb_Build

Which build: Latest Successful

Files: **/*

ğŸ“Œ Pipeline example
steps {
    copyArtifacts(
        projectName: 'MavenWeb_Build',
        selector: lastSuccessful()
    )
}

